The hydrodynamic forces Fx and Fy acting on the shaft can be expressed as
(10){FxFy}=-∑i=14[cos(ϕi+αi)-sin(ϕi+αi)sin(ϕi+αi)cos(ϕi+αi)]{FniFti}
where ϕi is the pivoting angle of the ith pad around the bearing.

The injected oil pressure in the ports of the servo valves can be obtained by solving the following equation (Santos, 1993):
(12)[V0/βf00V0/βf]{P·1P·3}+[KPQ+πdT4128μlT-KPQ-KPQKPQ+πdT4128μlT]   ×{P1P3}+{-11}QVI=πdT4128μlT{p¯1p¯3}
where Pi is the oil injection pressure in the ith pad, p¯i is the average hydrodynamic pressure in the gap of the ith pad, KPQ is an empirical constant, V0 is the pipeline inner volume, βf is the oil compressibility factor, and dT and lT are the diameter and length of the pipeline.
